This paper focuses on analyzing the differences in scientific writing styles between native English-speaking scholars (NESs) and non-native English-speaking scholars (NNESs). The paper uses a large-scale dataset of articles published in PLoS, which is a multidisciplinary journal that covers various fields including computer science. The paper's focus on linguistic complexity and its examination of syntactic and lexical complexity align with several sub-categories in computer science, including computational linguistics (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), deep learning (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and natural language processing (cs.NE).
